lifting, Dirty Water tells how even the most polluted water can be cleaned up-by ordinary people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnvironmental policyzCaliforniazSanta Monica Bay Region. 0aEnvironmentalistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aHigh school teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMarine pollutionzCaliforniazSanta Monica BayxPrevention. 0aPolitical activistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSewage disposal in the oceanxEnvironmental aspectszCaliforniazSanta Monica Bay. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  a1985.  abays and oceans.  abeach.  abodies of water.  aclean water act.  aclean water.  addt.  adirty water.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aecology.  aengaging.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental impact.  aenvironmental movement.  aheal the bay.  ahuman impact.  ainsecticide pollution.  ainspirational.  alively.  alocal politics.  alos angeles.  amake a difference.  anonfiction account.  apolluted water.  araw sewage.  asanta monica bay.  ascientists.  asea floor.  aswimming.  atrue story.  auplifting.  awater pollution.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094475640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944756423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944756/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles